e contexte de l'époque.  aThis volume contains the definitive version of the second of the five volumes of Benjamin Constant's major study entitled "De la Religion, considérée dans sa source .". Its unusually extensive annexes assemble a selection of manuscripts illustrating the working methods and strategies employed by the author. Further, the volume contains a general introduction, a chronology and a detailed critical apparatus comprising explanatory notes, biographical details of the persons referred to, a bibliography, and an index of proper names. As such it gives a graphic idea of the astounding originality displayed by Constant in his approach to research on religion.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn French.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 4aConstant, Benjamin. 4aFrankreich – Literatur. 4aFrankreich – Literaturgeschichte. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aDeguise, Pierre, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKloocke, Kurt.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies - 1990 - 1999z9783110637830oZDB-23-GLC0 cprintz978348450418940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311092377340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110923773423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110923773/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-GLCc1990d1999